.TH "__iavf_get_coalesce" 9 "__iavf_get_coalesce" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__iavf_get_coalesce \- get per-queue coalesce settings
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __iavf_get_coalesce
.BI "(struct net_device *netdev "  ","
.BI "struct ethtool_coalesce *ec "  ","
.BI "int queue "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "netdev" 12
the netdev to check
.IP "ec" 12
ethtool coalesce data structure
.IP "queue" 12
which queue to pick
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Gets the per-queue settings for coalescence. Specifically Rx and Tx usecs
are per queue. If queue is <0 then we default to queue 0 as the
representative value.
